\taxon{Proposition}
\title{Transition density of Brownian Vector}

\p{
  Let #{ (B_{t} )_{t\geq 0} } be a [Brownian Motion](SP-0001), then the density of #{ \left( B_{t_1}, B_{t_2} \dots B_{t_n}   \right)  } is given by
  ##{
    f_{B_{t_1} \dots  B_{t_n} } (x_1, \dots x_n) = 
    p_{t_1} (x_1) 
    p_{t_2 - t_1} (x_2 - x_1) \dots 
    p_{t_n - t_{n-1}} (x_n - x_{n-1})
  }

  whre #{ p_{t}  } is the [transition density](SP-000D)
}